# Dictation Manager Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and adjust the paths for your system

# ============================================================
# INSTALLATION PATHS (Required - adjust for your system)
# ============================================================

# Application directory (where this project is located)
# Linux example:
APP_DIR=/home/tho/soft/ai/dictation
# macOS example:
# APP_DIR=/Users/username/nerd-gui

# nerd-dictation installation directory (OPTIONAL)
# Defaults to apps/nerd-dictation if not specified or path doesn't exist
# Only set this if you want to use a custom nerd-dictation installation
# Linux example:
NERD_DICTATION_DIR=/home/tho/app_folder/nerd-dictation
# macOS example:
# NERD_DICTATION_DIR=/Users/username/nerd-gui/apps/nerd-dictation

# Vosk models directory
# Linux example:
MODELS_DIR=/home/tho/.config/nerd-dictation
# macOS example:
# MODELS_DIR=/Users/username/Library/Application Support/nerd-dictation

# ============================================================
# PLATFORM-SPECIFIC NOTES
# ============================================================
#
# Linux (Ubuntu):
#   - Uses CUDA for GPU acceleration (NVIDIA)
#   - Uses xdotool for keyboard output
#   - Models stored in ~/.config/nerd-dictation
#
# macOS (Apple Silicon):
#   - Uses CPU with int8 quantization (optimized for Apple Silicon)
#   - Uses PyAutoGUI for keyboard output (requires Accessibility permissions)
#   - Models stored in ~/Library/Application Support/nerd-dictation
#   - IMPORTANT: Grant Accessibility permissions in System Preferences >
#                Privacy & Security > Accessibility
#
# ============================================================
# NOTE: All other settings (backend, models, parameters) are
# now configured via the GUI Settings window and stored in
# the database. No need to edit this file for configuration!
# ============================================================
